A time-amplitude algorithm, which involves manually placing 'hoops' to specify where the detected spike waveform must go through to be classified as a defined unit.

The system calculates the first three principle components on a representative sample group then projects each new waveform into the same 3D PCA space. The user draws manually an ellipsoid around each cluster to sort the group.

Waveform sample points are projected into a feature space contaiining a high- and a low-frequency component of the waveforms on its axis. A histogram is constructed. Clusters are then estimated by determining peaks and valleys and are sorted into units.
